[{"id":40867,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Gravitation","question":"","options":["Statement I is correct but Statement II is incorrect","Statement I is incorrect but Statement II is correct","Both Statement I and Statement II are correct","Both Statement I and Statement II are incorrect"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math>&nbsp;be the mass of the satellite.</p><p>The potential energy of the satellite is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>The velocity of the satellite is given by&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>Kinetic energy is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>The total mechanical energy is the sum of potential and kinetic energy. So,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>K</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Hence, both the statements are false.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40942,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Gravitation","question":"","options":["Both&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> are correct and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;is the correct explanation of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>","Both&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;are correct but&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is NOT&nbsp;the correct explanation of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;is not correct but&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is correct","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;is correct but <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;is not correct"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mi>e</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>GM</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></p><p>Hence reason <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;is not correct.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40984,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Gravitation","question":"","options":["<math><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mi> </mi><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>,</mo></math><br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mo>/</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mrow></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mo>/</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mrow></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2G</mn><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>f</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>.</mo><mi>&#160;</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr)","image":null},{"id":40919,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Gravitation","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>G</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn><mi>G</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>G</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>60</mn><mi>G</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0ca9f7f2-e5be-4c01-a6f8-df8ce9489288-97701065-e1b4-4af1-a16d-56dd9884b1bf-image.png\" style=\"width: 273px; height: 249px;\" /></p><p>Use the formula&nbsp;of the gravitational potential in terms of universal gravitational constant,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>50</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>25</mn></mfrac></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>G</mi></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41002,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Gravitation","question":"","options":["$6.73 \\times 10^{-5} \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$","$6.73 \\times 10^{-3} \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$","$6.73 \\times 10^{-2} \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$","$6.73 \\times 10^{-4} \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$"],"answer":0,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (22 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":40960,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Gravitation","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ce84c78e-d5c4-4bfb-b928-6cf2e56f6a4a-image.png\" /></p><p><math><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><msub><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><msub><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math><mo>&#8756;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (08 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41006,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Gravitation","question":"","options":["$r$","$r^{-1}$","$r^2$","$r^{-2}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"Acceleration due to gravity at depth d from the surface of the earth or at a distance $r$ from the centre ' $O$ ' of the earth $g^{\\prime}=\\frac{4}{3} \\pi \\rho G r$ Hence $g^{\\prime} \\propto r$\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6W_urH2LBpJ6bY8iBj8seUOML61frWDSdYocY29cF4s.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (12 May Online)","image":null},{"id":40849,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Gravitation","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi>R</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mi>R</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>The acceleration due to gravity at a height <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> above the surface of the Earth is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>g</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>h</mi><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>The acceleration due to gravity at a depth <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> below the surface of the Earth is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>g</mi><mi>q</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>R</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>According to the given problem,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>g</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>g</mi><mi>q</mi></msub><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Equations (1), (2) and (3) imply that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>g</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>R</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>R</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>R</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>4</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Take <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p><p>So, from equation (4), it follows that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>(</mo><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (29 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40846,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Gravitation","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>R</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>R</mi><mi>E</mi></msub><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>E</mi></msub><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Escape velocity is given by, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>Therefore,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>E</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>G</mi><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>E</mi></msub></mrow><msub><mi>R</mi><mi>E</mi></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>G</mi><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>P</mi></msub></mrow><msub><mi>R</mi><mi>P</mi></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>i</mi><mi>i</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>E</mi></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>P</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>E</mi></msub><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (30 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41012,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Gravitation","question":"","options":["Statement $-1$ is false, Statement $-2$ is true.","Statement $-1$ is true, Statement $-2$ is true; Statement $-2$ is correct explanation for Statement-1.","Statement $-1$ is true, Statement $-2$ is true; Statement $-2$ is not a correct explanation for Statement-1.","Statement $-1$ is true, Statement $-2$ is False."],"answer":1,"solution":"$$\n\\mathrm{g}=\\mathrm{GM} / \\mathrm{r}^2\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2008","image":null}]